12:37.678 --> 12:40.747
First Unitarian. It's very open-minded.

12:40.748 --> 12:42.637
There's a joy mass tonight,

12:42.638 --> 12:44.657
with lots of people singing and dancing.

12:44.658 --> 12:45.627
Mm.

12:45.628 --> 12:47.587
Well, I sat through "Godspell" once.

12:47.588 --> 12:49.028
I don't think I'm gonna do it again.

12:49.936 --> 12:51.657
I think we'll just
stick with our religion

12:51.658 --> 12:53.557
that wasn't founded last Thursday.

12:53.558 --> 12:55.527
Well... Think about it.

12:55.528 --> 12:57.657
It's open 24 hours so
that homeless people

12:57.658 --> 12:59.747
and sex workers have a place to sleep.

13:00.748 --> 13:02.078
Wow.

13:02.248 --> 13:04.637
She looks so much older in person.

13:04.638 --> 13:06.647
Wait, what? How would you
know what she looks like?

13:06.648 --> 13:08.727
I saw a picture of her
with her dirty vegetables

13:08.728 --> 13:10.597
on your phone.

13:10.598 --> 13:12.727
You went through my phone?

13:12.728 --> 13:14.667
That is unbelievable!

13:14.668 --> 13:17.627
Well... Technically, that is my phone.

13:17.628 --> 13:19.717
Just like your belly
is technically my belly,

13:19.718 --> 13:22.537
even if some other
mother wants to fill it

13:22.538 --> 13:24.737
full of her extra-starchy rice!

13:24.738 --> 13:27.677
- Whoo!
- Yeah!

13:27.678 --> 13:29.577
Yeah! Whoo!

13:30.678 --> 13:31.657
Yeah!

13:31.658 --> 13:32.627
Whoo!

13:32.628 --> 13:33.587
Yeah, Dad!

13:33.588 --> 13:34.717
Whoo!

13:39.608 --> 13:41.557
Mrs. O'Malley has two D.U.I.S?

13:41.558 --> 13:43.617
Hello, "A" in history.

13:49.608 --> 13:50.717
Aaaaaah!

13:50.718 --> 13:53.607
Okay, okay, okay, okay, okay, okay, okay!

13:55.568 --> 13:57.991
Yeah! Tokyo drift, bitch!

13:58.114 --> 13:59.707
That's why you hang with Dad, huh?

13:59.708 --> 14:00.747
Best day ever!

14:00.748 --> 14:02.567
All right, let's wrap it up,

14:02.568 --> 14:04.587
take this party back to my basement.

14:04.588 --> 14:06.557
Wait. Just one more thing.

14:06.558 --> 14:07.667
Backwards high-speed chase.

14:11.598 --> 14:13.398
Jimmy, no, no, no! You're
heading towards a...

14:19.548 --> 14:22.578
The grandkids are gonna
love this story, papa.

14:25.618 --> 14:28.537
Now, when they get to
the final runway show,

14:28.538 --> 14:29.637
we have to rank them

14:29.638 --> 14:31.697
and see if our choices
match up with the judges'.

14:31.698 --> 14:34.537
But they're all so talented.
Everyone should get an "A."

14:34.538 --> 14:35.747
Like I said, we have to wait.

14:35.748 --> 14:37.618
Everyone's a winner!

14:38.668 --> 14:40.598
Oh, yeah... more popcorn.

14:43.668 --> 14:45.657
I decided to give you another chance

14:45.658 --> 14:48.567
to come down and watch
"Project Runway" with me.

14:48.568 --> 14:49.747
Jodi keeps calling it "runaways."

14:49.748 --> 14:51.667
It's driving me crazy.

14:51.668 --> 14:52.687
Where are you going?

14:52.688 --> 14:53.757
Sandra's church.

14:53.758 --> 14:55.637
You absolutely are not!

14:55.638 --> 14:57.717
Afterward, Sandra and I
might watch another "runway."

14:57.718 --> 14:59.577
Maybe even "runway all stars."

14:59.578 --> 15:01.667
- You don't mean that.
- Oh, I absolutely do!

15:01.668 --> 15:04.537
I can see how a mom like
Sandra could lure you in,

15:04.538 --> 15:05.677
with her rainbow toe socks

15:05.678 --> 15:07.727
and that smile she throws
around like a weapon.

15:07.728 --> 15:09.547
That is not what it is.

15:09.548 --> 15:11.747
She accepts me. She accepts mesh.

15:11.748 --> 15:13.567
She accepts all of it.

15:13.568 --> 15:14.647
I do better than accept you.

15:14.648 --> 15:16.587
I protect you from
going out into the world

15:16.588 --> 15:17.657
and being judged by people

15:17.658 --> 15:19.627
based on some ridiculous
thing you're wearing.

15:19.628 --> 15:20.737
I don't have to go out into the world.

15:20.738 --> 15:22.698
I'm getting plenty of
judgment right here at home.

15:26.618 --> 15:28.577
As Heidi Klum would say, bon voyage.

15:30.650 --> 15:32.719
Brad, please get off the couch.

15:34.614 --> 15:35.614
Brad.

15:38.067 --> 15:40.037
Thank you.

15:43.947 --> 15:45.066
Are divorced people

15:45.067 --> 15:47.036
allowed to give each
other parenting advice?

15:47.037 --> 15:49.046
I just let my kids trash a cop car,

15:49.047 --> 15:51.136
and then to punish them,
I took them out for froyo.

15:51.137 --> 15:53.076
Well, that's nothing.

15:53.077 --> 15:55.986
Kenny went to church with another mom.

15:55.987 --> 15:56.996
Catholic?

15:56.997 --> 15:59.046
Unitarian.

15:59.047 --> 16:00.966
Whoa.

16:00.967 --> 16:03.076
He says it's because I don't accept him.

16:03.077 --> 16:04.046
You don't.

16:04.047 --> 16:05.156
Wha...

16:05.157 --> 16:07.077
I accept most of him.

16:08.967 --> 16:11.996
Well, kids always come
back to their moms.

16:11.997 --> 16:13.136
It's the dads that have to worry.

16:13.137 --> 16:15.046
I mean, I live 10 stairs away from them,

16:15.047 --> 16:16.156
and they barely come to visit.

16:16.157 --> 16:18.026
What's gonna happen when I move out?

16:18.027 --> 16:19.086
That depends.

16:19.087 --> 16:21.046
Is your new house gonna
smell like dog poo?

16:22.067 --> 16:24.126
I keep looking for it,
but I cannot find it.

16:24.127 --> 16:26.631
Well, just get the kids down
here and have them look for it.

16:26.795 --> 16:28.106
They're not gonna want to do that.

16:28.107 --> 16:29.707
Just tell them what you want them to do,

16:29.727 --> 16:31.252
and eventually, they'll get on board.

16:31.370 --> 16:33.036
You need to take a firmer hand.

16:33.037 --> 16:34.156
Well, maybe I am too soft on them,

16:34.157 --> 16:35.966
but when it comes to Kenny,

16:35.967 --> 16:37.673
I think you're a little bit too hard.

16:42.987 --> 16:44.106
It's in your shoe.

16:52.097 --> 16:54.986
Well, this is... new.

16:54.987 --> 16:57.966
Yeah, super-new and super-casual.

16:57.967 --> 17:00.036
Got jeans under my robe.

17:00.037 --> 17:02.166
Wow, Jesus. Boyfriend jeans.

17:02.167 --> 17:04.116
Yeah. Borrowed them from St. Peter.

17:05.311 --> 17:07.996
So, uh, you feeling
guilty about something?

17:07.997 --> 17:09.976
No, I'm not guilty.

17:09.977 --> 17:12.046
If Mom can't accept me for who I am,

17:12.047 --> 17:14.027
then I'm just gonna
be with people who can.

17:15.097 --> 17:16.946
Can't argue with that.

17:18.117 --> 17:20.106
Kenny. You made it.

17:22.067 --> 17:23.067
Come in.

17:26.107 --> 17:29.146
Uh, is this a "bring your own
tambourine" situation, or...

17:29.147 --> 17:31.116
- Oh, no. They're provided.
- Oh.

17:31.117 --> 17:33.146
Hi. Joy to you.

17:33.147 --> 17:35.126
I'd like to introduce you to Kenny.

17:35.127 --> 17:36.106
He's our newest member.

17:36.107 --> 17:37.126
Hi. Hello. Okay.

17:37.127 --> 17:40.026
Uh, joy to everyone.

17:40.027 --> 17:41.976
Joy to you.

17:41.977 --> 17:43.026
O... Kay.

17:43.027 --> 17:44.106
Welcome. Welcome.

17:45.117 --> 17:47.166
Oh. Okay.

17:47.167 --> 17:49.126
Ohh! So many hugs.

17:51.997 --> 17:53.056
Mom.

17:53.057 --> 17:55.096
Eileen. Hi.

17:55.097 --> 17:56.106
Joy to you.

17:56.107 --> 17:57.066
Uh-huh.

17:57.067 --> 17:58.986
Hello, Kenny.

17:58.987 --> 18:01.116
Um, Mom, uh, what are you doing here?

18:01.117 --> 18:02.259
Well...

18:02.395 --> 18:06.026
Another woman isn't gonna
bring my son to church.

18:06.027 --> 18:07.387
If this is where you want to be...

18:09.147 --> 18:10.987
I want to be here for you.

18:14.037 --> 18:16.067
Ohhhh... Boy.

18:17.937 --> 18:19.087
Okay.

18:21.520 --> 18:22.520
Hi!

18:26.117 --> 18:30.116
Sisters and brothers, let
us bow our heads and pray.

18:30.117 --> 18:31.937
That, I can do.

18:33.077 --> 18:35.056
To whom it may concern...

18:35.057 --> 18:37.100
No. I'm out. I'm sorry.

18:37.265 --> 18:38.777
Kenny, this is not a church.

18:38.882 --> 18:41.026
This is a bus station in Weirdoville.

18:41.027 --> 18:42.027
I can't do this.

18:43.997 --> 18:45.956
All these jeans. What is this, a mall?

18:45.957 --> 18:48.136
Is that guy hacky-sacking?

18:48.137 --> 18:50.106
But ultimately, we must figure out...

18:50.107 --> 18:52.156
Hey!

18:52.157 --> 18:54.167
I can't believe she left.

18:56.967 --> 18:58.977
I can't believe she came.

19:00.937 --> 19:04.026
Okay, Dad, where are
you taking us? Bowling?

19:04.027 --> 19:05.429
Ooh! Ooh! The Bahamas?

19:05.556 --> 19:08.694
Nope. We're gonna stay right
here and play with your dog.

19:08.695 --> 19:10.046
But... We don't want to do that.

19:10.047 --> 19:11.046
I don't care.

19:11.047 --> 19:13.016
Now, teach Brad how to fetch.

19:13.017 --> 19:14.016
I know you can do it.

19:14.017 --> 19:15.936
Dad, it doesn't fetch. Okay?

19:15.937 --> 19:17.146
It doesn't do anything.

19:17.147 --> 19:18.997
This plan is a huge bomb.

19:21.037 --> 19:23.076
Whoa! Look at him go!

19:23.077 --> 19:24.106
A bomb!

19:24.107 --> 19:26.096
He was on the bomb squad.

19:26.097 --> 19:28.016
Oh, my God. Look how happy he is!

19:28.017 --> 19:29.126
Come here!

19:29.127 --> 19:31.136
Who got the bomb, huh?
Yeah, you got the bomb!

19:31.137 --> 19:32.669
Jimmy, let's see what else he can do.

19:32.670 --> 19:34.056
Pretend you're attacking me.

19:34.057 --> 19:36.116
No, no! Don't do that. He
will literally kill you.

19:36.117 --> 19:37.966
He is trained to find drugs, though.

19:37.967 --> 19:39.156
Find the drugs.

19:39.157 --> 19:41.106
Who's got the dope? Who's got the dope?

19:42.153 --> 19:44.076
He's making a beeline for next door.

19:44.077 --> 19:45.136
Oh, my...

19:45.137 --> 19:46.712
Mrs. Novich has glaucoma!

19:46.713 --> 19:48.967
Brad!

19:53.107 --> 19:57.066
I can't tell... is that
a dress or an oil spill?

19:57.067 --> 20:00.086
It's definitely a natural disaster.

20:00.087 --> 20:01.586
So, how was the rest of church?

20:01.587 --> 20:04.096
I don't know. I, uh, left a
little after you, actually.

20:04.097 --> 20:05.156
You did? Why?

20:05.157 --> 20:06.575
Was it the tambourines

20:06.576 --> 20:08.136
or the white people with dreadlocks?

20:08.137 --> 20:11.146
It was...

20:11.147 --> 20:13.046
Neither of those things.

20:14.567 --> 20:17.096
It just didn't feel right.

20:17.097 --> 20:18.936
You know? It wasn't mine.

20:20.578 --> 20:23.036
Maybe my mom doesn't fully accept me now,

20:23.037 --> 20:25.126
but at least she's proved

20:25.127 --> 20:28.017
she's willing to start taking baby steps.

20:29.704 --> 20:31.116
Maybe you do look good in mesh.

20:31.117 --> 20:33.066
Oh, God. No, Mom. Mesh is not my thing.

20:33.067 --> 20:34.086
You were very right.

20:34.087 --> 20:36.066
Oh, thank God. Because I didn't mean it.

20:36.067 --> 20:38.066
I also cleaned out
everything in your closet

20:38.067 --> 20:39.957
that wasn't Navy or tan.

20:40.957 --> 20:43.093
I'm sorry, but this is a process.

20:48.981 --> 20:51.309
Okay, thank you for letting
me take another crack at this.

20:51.317 --> 20:53.992
Now, this is just the
one that shows my arms.

20:56.022 --> 20:58.141
See? It's just a whisper of mesh.

20:58.142 --> 21:00.131
What do you think?

21:00.132 --> 21:02.971
Honestly...

21:02.972 --> 21:04.991
It looks like your arms are two pale eels

21:04.992 --> 21:07.011
trying to escape a Fisherman's net.

21:07.012 --> 21:09.041
Tim Gunn, what do you think?

21:09.042 --> 21:10.981
Well, it definitely makes a statement.

21:10.982 --> 21:15.142
And the statement is, "my
gym membership has lapsed."

21:19.152 --> 21:20.731
Okay.

